etymologies: 1940s (originally US): so named because it was first used to denote a parachutist's garment

definitions: a garment incorporating trousers and a sleeved top in one piece, worn as a fashion item, protective garment, or uniform

examples.text: she wore a tight silver jumpsuit

shortDefinitions: garment incorporating trousers and sleeved top in one piece, worn as fashion item, protective garment
